    {
      "receptor_id": "calix-7",
      "name": "Calix[4]arene derivative 7 bearing amino and imidazole groups",
      "description": "p-tert-butylcalix[4]arene functionalized with amino and imidazole groups; paper-highlighted best-performing sensor coating for MC; coated on QCM gold electrode by drop-casting from 1.0 mM chloroform solution",
      "charge_class": "neutral",
      "structure_known": "yes",
      "smiles_or_structure_text": "p-tert-butylcalix[4]arene scaffold (all 4 para-tert-butyl) with 1,3-distal lower-rim -O-CH2-CH2-NH-CH2-CH2-(1H-imidazol-1-yl) pendant arms (secondary amine + N-alkylimidazole); the other 1,3-distal pair of lower-rim oxygens are methylated (-O-CH3). Verified directly from Fig. 1 of the paper: R1 = CH2CH2NHCH2CH2-imidazolyl, R2 = Me.",
      "smiles": "C(C)(C)(C)c1cc2cc(c1OCCNCCn3ccnc3)Cc4cc(C(C)(C)C)cc(c4OC)Cc5cc(C(C)(C)C)cc(c5OCCNCCn6ccnc6)Cc7cc(C(C)(C)C)cc(c7OC)C2",
      "smiles_basis": "from_figure",
      "smiles_verified": true,
      "smiles_corrected": true,
      "original_smiles": "CC(C)(C)c1cc2Cc3cc(C(C)(C)C)cc(Cc4cc(C(C)(C)C)cc(Cc5cc(C(C)(C)C)cc(Cc(c1OCC(=O)NCCn1ccnc1)2)c5OCC(=O)NCCn1ccnc1)c4O)c3O",
      "correction_reason": "Original SMILES was invalid (could not be kekulized by RDKit) AND used incorrect pendant chemistry. Direct inspection of Fig. 1 in the PDF shows: Calix-7 R1 = -CH2CH2-NH-CH2CH2-(N1-imidazolyl) (a secondary amine arm, NOT an amide -OCH2C(=O)NH- arm). Also R2 = Me, meaning the other 1,3-distal lower-rim oxygens are methylated (-OMe), NOT free OH. The figure shows all four para positions bearing tert-butyl. Reconstructed canonical SMILES (C60H82N6O4, MW 950.64) parses cleanly in RDKit and matches Fig. 1 connectivity exactly.",
      "notes": "Exact structure shown in Fig. 1. Pendant arm verified verbatim from figure: R1 = -CH2CH2-NH-CH2CH2-imidazol-1-yl; R2 = Me; calix scaffold has 4 p-tert-butyl groups and 1,3-distal di-O-alkylation/di-O-methylation. Cone vs partial-cone conformation not specified by the figure (drawn flat); SMILES omits stereochemistry. Reference [29] (Tabakci 2012, Tetrahedron 68, 4182-4186) cited for synthesis."
    }
